The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning to discover collusion strategies in a winner-take-all framework. This topic falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of reinforcement learning also suggests that the paper may fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the analysis of signaling mechanisms and communication channels suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of social and information sciences (cs.SI) and systems and control (cs.SY).
